    <h1 style="text-align: center; text-decoration: underline;">How To Take Care Of Your Pet</h1>

    <section id="dog-care">
        <h2>Dog Care</h2>
        <p>Welcome to the joy of dog ownership! Caring for a dog is rewarding and requires responsibility. Here's how to ensure your dog is happy, healthy, and well-behaved.</p>

        <h3>Basic Needs</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Food & Water:</strong> Provide balanced meals twice a day and fresh water at all times.</li>
            <li><strong>Shelter:</strong> Ensure a comfortable and safe sleeping area.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Health Care</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Regular Vet Visits:</strong> Annual check-ups and vaccinations.</li>
            <li><strong>Exercise:</strong> Daily walks and playtime to keep them fit.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Training & Behavior</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Basic Commands:</strong> Teach commands like sit, stay, and come.</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section id="cat-care">
        <h2>Cat Care</h2>
        <p>Cats make wonderful companions. Here are some essentials for taking good care of your feline friend.</p>

        <h3>Basic Needs</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Food & Water:</strong> Provide a steady supply of fresh water and meals tailored to their age, health, and lifestyle.</li>
            <li><strong>Litter Box:</strong> Keep a clean and accessible litter box.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Health Care</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Regular Vet Visits:</strong> Yearly exams and preventive care.</li>
            <li><strong>Grooming:</strong> Regular brushing to reduce shedding and hairballs.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Safety Tips</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Identification:</strong> Microchipping and a collar with ID tags.</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

